               <msContents>
                  <summary>Recto contains the beginning of a letter in which the basmalla is lost, but which contains well-known opening letterformulae in the first line, informing the addressee that the sender's family is well ('[I wrote] my letter to you, may God support you, while those with me [are in good health]'). The sender requests that the addressee does something immediately ('the moment that [you receive this letter of mine]') and mentions a third person.</summary>
                  <msItem>
                     <note type="general">Recto (perpendicular to fibres) contains 4 lines and has a small blank margin at the top.</note>
                     <note type="general">The verso contains a fragment of a letter. See nyu.apis.5376.</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="ar-Arab">Arabic</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
